    • responseDojoMultipartConfig

      public static void responseDojoMultipartConfig​(java.io.Writer Out, java.lang.String JsonExportName, JSONable Obj) throws java.lang.Exception
      When using client-side frameworks such as Dojo that may use an iFrame for ajax-contents, the protocol is typically yo return the json data packaged inside a textarea. This function does that. It is exactly equivalent to the "plain" response method except the jsonable object is output inside a textarea and the writer is expected to be set up as an HTML one.
      Parameters:
      Out -
      JsonExportName -
      Obj -
      Throws:
      java.lang.Exception
